# Pin pip itself in every lock. Without this, `pip install -r
# requirements/<lock>.txt` is mediated by whatever pip the runner image
# happens to ship — the only unhashed network fetch in the otherwise
# fully hash-verified install chain. A compromised pip can ignore
# --require-hashes and silently bypass every other pin in the lock.
#
# Pinning pip alongside the rest of the lock means the bootstrap pip
# downloads pip==X.Y.Z under hash verification before it becomes the
# resolver for everything else. Consumed by tools/scripts/regenerate-locks.sh.
pip
